1 AN ACT
2 RELATING TO AEROSPACE; CREATING THE SPACE COMMISSION WORKING
3 GROUP; PROVIDING DUTIES; REQUIRING A FINAL REPORT.
4
5 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF NEW MEXICO:
6 SECTION 1. TEMPORARY PROVISION--SPACE COMMISSION
7 WORKING GROUP--CREATED--DUTIES--FINAL REPORT.--
8 A. The "space commission working group" is created
9 to study and make recommendations on the feasibility of
10 establishing a space commission and drafting a proposal for
11 the structure and scope of the space commission. The working
12 group shall consist of:
13 (1) one member appointed by the governor;
14 (2) one member appointed by the lieutenant
15 governor;
16 (3) one member appointed by the president
17 pro tempore of the senate;
18 (4) one member appointed by the speaker of
19 the house of representatives;
20 (5) one member appointed by the minority
21 floor leader of the house of representatives; and
22 (6) one member appointed by the minority
23 floor leader of the senate.
24 B. In making appointments to the space commission
25 working group, prioritization shall be made for persons with HB 96/a
Page 1

1 experience in commercial aerospace, civil aviation, space
2 economic development, space-related academic research and
3 nonprofit work that supports the space economy.
4 C. Appointment of members to the space commission
5 working group shall be made by July 1, 2026. Members
6 appointed shall serve at the pleasure of the appointing
7 officer. A vacancy shall be filled within thirty days after
8 the vacancy occurs in the manner of the original appointment.
9 D. The space commission working group shall elect
10 a chair from its membership. The working group shall meet at
11 the call of the chair or at the request of a majority of its
12 members, as necessary to carry out its duties, but not less
13 than once per month. A majority of the members constitutes a
14 quorum for the transaction of business, and the support of a
15 majority of the members is required for adoption of any
16 action.
17 E. The space commission working group shall study
18 and develop a report of its recommendations regarding the
19 establishment of a space commission, including:
20 (1) the feasibility of establishing a space
21 commission as the statewide authority for the aerospace
22 industry;
23 (2) the identification of key stakeholders
24 currently involved in civil and commercial aerospace;
25 (3) a strategic plan for the space HB 96/a
Page 2

1 commission that details its authority, scope of work and
2 responsibilities, including educational and workforce
3 pathways; and
4 (4) the design for a board of directors for
5 the space commission, including the composition of its
6 members, structure, scope of work, responsibilities and
7 budgetary requirements.
8 F. By October 1, 2026, the space commission
9 working group shall report its findings and recommendations
10 to the interim legislative committee that studies economic
11 development.
12 G. Members of the space commission working group
13 are entitled to receive per diem and mileage as provided in
14 the Per Diem and Mileage Act and shall receive no other
15 compensation, perquisite or allowance for their service on
16 the working group.
17 H. The economic development department shall
18 provide the necessary staff and administrative support to the
19 space commission working group, and the department may hire
20 one staff member to support the space commission working
21 group.
22 I. The space commission working group shall be
23 dissolved effective December 31, 2026. HB 96/a
